Real Madrid Beats Tottenham 4-0 in Champions League; Schalke Defeats Inter

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-05T20:41:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/real-madrid-beats-tottenham-4-0-in-champions-league-schalke-defeats-inter.html
Real Madrid defeated 10-man
Tottenham 4-0 in the opening game of their Champions League
soccer quarterfinal, while Schalke beat defending champion Inter
Milan 5-2.  Emmanuel Adebayor scored two goals and Angel Di Maria and
Cristiano Ronaldo had one each for nine-time European champion
Real. Tottenhamâ€™s  Peter Crouch  was sent off in the 17th minute
after picking up his second yellow card.  Edu scored twice as Schalke overcame allowing a goal in the
opening minute to beat Inter in Milan. Schalke also got scores
from Joel Matip and Raul Gonzalez, along with own goal by Inter
defender Andrea Rannochia. Dejan Stankovic and  Diego Milito 
scored for Inter.  Tottenham and Schalke will host the return games in the
two-match series on April 13.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
